input.content:
TASK: Read the mathematical statement.
If the statement is true, describe a proof strategy.
If the statement is false, provide a counter-example and explain it.
If you can neither produce a counter-example nor a proof, indicate that you have no solution to this problem, and briefly describe the state of the art conjectures or results, if any.
For any set $X$ and any involutive function $f : X \to X$, every section $s : X \to X$ of $f$ is equal to $f$.

example.output: t.union(t.str, t.dict({"counter-example": t.str}), t.dict({"proof-strategy": t.str}), t.literal("no-solution"))
